gomodel:SYNGO_3723  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: FIGURE 6: Stx4 knock down blocks TfR-SEP membrane insertion following stimulation with Bic/Gly suggesting Syntaxin-4 mediates activity-triggered exocytosis in dendrites/spines\nFIGURE 7: Stx4 deltaTM prevents LTP in Schaffer collaterals. LTP was induced by depolarizing the cell to 0 mV and delivering 200 stimuli at 2 Hz. Using standard intracellular solution, this induction protocol reliably triggered robust sustained potentiation of EPSC amplitudes to 172 ± 18% of baseline (Figure 7A). However, LTP was almost completely abolished (EPSC amplitudes 111 ± 19% of baseline) when purified Stx4DTM (2.5 mM) was included in the recording solution.\n\n19/6/2018 Pim\n- Fig.3: \"AMPA Receptors are Directly Inserted Into the Spine Plasma Membrane\"\n- Fig.5: \"Stx4 Marks Sites of Exocytosis at the Spine Membrane\". Experimental description: M&M: Hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from E18 RAT embryos\nLTP experiments were performed using transverse hippocampal slices cut from C57Bl/6 MICE (350 mm," ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3723" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

